'''Steve Bodow''' is Executive Producer and former head writer for [[The Daily Show with Jon Stewart]].

He is also a founding member and a past artistic director of the New York theater group [[Elevator Repair Service]],<ref>[http://www.elevator.org/ Elevator Repair Service: Home<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> best known for ''Gatz'', its full-text adaptation of ''[[The Great Gatsby]]''.

Before joining The Daily Show in 2002, Bodow was a journalist for [[Wired (magazine)|Wired]], [[New York Magazine]], [[Salon.com]] and the [[New York Times Magazine]]. He grew up in Rye, NY, graduating Rye High School, [[Yale University]], and NYU's [[Interactive Telecommunications Program]].  While at Yale, Bodow co-founded the improv group [[Just Add Water (improv troupe)|Just Add Water]].<ref>[http://www.yaledailynews.com/news/2007/feb/05/yale-alumni-move-up-in-the-world-of-comedy/ Yale alumni move up in the world of comedy]</ref>

